verbose_text: The first contributions to the interaction energy for trans-Me 2 come again from the atom pairs of the central moiety lying within the sphere with R S = 1.6 A, increase of R S by DeltaR S = ~ 0.4 A includes the carbon atoms of the methyl groups and therefore gives a large contribution to the interaction energy, all contributing intermolecular atom pairs lie within a sphere with R S = 2.5 A (or DeltaR S = 0.9 A) and further enlargement of R S does not change E Das anymore.
